author: By KIM CHANDLER Associated Press
title: Governor: Alabama stay home order to remain through April
description: MONTGOMERY, Ala. (AP) — Alabama Gov. Kay Ivey said Tuesday she intends to keep a stay home order in place through April, striking a measured approach as some Southern states push to quickly reopen.
content:
We are not testing enough yet. We are little bit less than 1 percent of our population and we need to do a whole lot more testing to get up the speed, Ivey said.
